				Xott,<BR>
<BR>
Just who the heck are you?  I come to Everlore to get information about different aspects of the game, and to check on current events. I do NOT come here to listen to one individual stand on a proverbial soapbox and give a lecture about his/her opinions on how this game should be played.  All of us have heard things said in /shout or /ooc channels that we would have preferred not to have heard.  But do I categorize it as &quot;nonsense&quot;? No.  Do I suggest to these people that they not enjoy the game as they choose? No.  Do I allow other individuals whose definition of &quot;fun&quot; differs from mine to diminish my own gaming experience? No.<BR>
<BR>
Wake up Xott!  Everquest has a huge and diverse base of players.  As such, there will always be people (maybe even a significant number) who will participate in the game in a manner you (or I) do not approve of.  The only person you can control is yourself. And how you react to other individual's actions, and how much control you give them over YOUR gaming experience is totally up to YOU. That's a fact.  Deal with it.  Do not try to impose YOUR opinion of &quot;proper&quot; gameplay (or &quot;etiquette&quot;, as you call it) on others.<BR>
<BR>
JA<BR>

